//Congential heart disease - One chamber heart (single ventricle)


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Cardio MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
When I select 'Congential heart disease' tab
Then 'Congential heart disease' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'One chamber heart (single ventricle)' from 'Congential heart disease' dropdown menu
Then 'Add pathology' button is enabled
And 'Functional' radio button is enabled
And 'Anatomical' radio button is enabled

And 'Atrial septal defect (ASD)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Transposition of the great arteries (TGA)' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Functional' radio button
Then 'Left (hypoplastic left heart syndrome)' radio button is enabled
And 'Right (hypoplastic right heart syndrome)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Left (hypoplastic left heart syndrome)' radio button
Then 'Mitral valve dysplasia/atresia' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hypoplastic/atretic LVOT' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Right (hypoplastic right heart syndrome)' radio button
Then 'Tricuspidal atresia' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pulmonary atresia' checkbox is enabled


When I select 'Anatomical' radio button
Then 'Left' radio button is enabled
And 'Right' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Left' radio button
Then 'Double inlet (DILV)' radio button is enabled
And 'Single inlet' radio button is enabled
And 'Common inlet' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Right' radio button
Then 'Double inlet (DIRV)' radio button is enabled
And 'Single inlet' radio button is enabled
And 'Common inlet' radio button is enabled
